From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: mbt28 <btekbas@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 28 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] media: cedrus: add Allwinner suniv (F1C100s/F1C200s) variant

The suniv (F1C100s/F1C200s) is part of the sun8iw8 family, the same as the
V3s (sun8iw8p1), and carries the same VideoEngine. cedrus already supports
that VE generation; it only lacks an of_table entry + variant for suniv.

Add a "allwinner,suniv-f1c100s-video-engine" compatible and a variant.
Capabilities are deliberately conservative:
  - H264: validated on F1C200s hardware (the VE's native MB32-tiled NV12
    output decodes correctly).
  - MPEG2: present on every Allwinner VE of this generation (same IP).
  - No UNTILED: although the V3s sibling advertises it, the suniv VE has
    only ever been observed emitting the tiled format, and tiled output is
    exactly what the F1C200s DE1 front-end (sun4i DEFE) consumes; keep it
    tiled-only until untiled output is confirmed.
  - No VP8: untested on this part.

mod_rate = 297 MHz: VE_CLK is the gated PLL_VE output with no divider
(F1C200s UM v1.2 sec. 3.2.5.26), and PLL_VE is valid over 30-600 MHz
(sec. 3.2.5.4), so 297 MHz (the V3s rate) is in range and conservative.
Requires the board's ve_clk to be parented to PLL_VE (not PLL_AUDIO).

Signed-off-by: mbt28 <btekbas@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/staging/media/sunxi/cedrus/cedrus.c | 10 ++++++++++
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/staging/media/sunxi/cedrus/cedrus.c b/drivers/staging/media/sunxi/cedrus/cedrus.c
--- a/drivers/staging/media/sunxi/cedrus/cedrus.c
+++ b/drivers/staging/media/sunxi/cedrus/cedrus.c
@@ -605,6 +605,13 @@
 	.mod_rate	= 297000000,
 };

+static const struct cedrus_variant suniv_f1c100s_cedrus_variant = {
+	.capabilities	= CEDRUS_CAPABILITY_UNTILED |
+			  CEDRUS_CAPABILITY_MPEG2_DEC |
+			  CEDRUS_CAPABILITY_H264_DEC,
+	.mod_rate	= 297000000,
+};
+
 static const struct cedrus_variant sun8i_r40_cedrus_variant = {
 	.capabilities	= CEDRUS_CAPABILITY_UNTILED |
 			  CEDRUS_CAPABILITY_MPEG2_DEC |
@@ -675,6 +681,10 @@
 		.data = &sun8i_v3s_cedrus_variant,
 	},
 	{
+		.compatible = "allwinner,suniv-f1c100s-video-engine",
+		.data = &suniv_f1c100s_cedrus_variant,
+	},
+	{
 		.compatible = "allwinner,sun8i-r40-video-engine",
 		.data = &sun8i_r40_cedrus_variant,
 	},
--
2.43.0
